<br>
-<br>
The majority agrees that the removal of the intentions forum would be best for the Brell Serilis board.  A recruiting type forum that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  explicitly</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> prohibits &quot;intention&quot; type posting in the manner of the former board would be made to aid those looking for raid support.<br>
<br>
All other non-reservable type raids are considered free for all by default.  Specific cases may be argued for and voted for on the board.<br>
<br>
Note: First Come, First Serve is the basis for which the &quot;free for all&quot; refered to above is founded on.<br>
-<br>
<br>
After looking through all the arguements, I noted that each one shared the same common threads: the agreement that intentions were causing problems, a need to help lower guilds gather support, and the ability to add reservated areas as needed.  I feel that my above proposal encorporates all those thoughts and is the best solution for our problem.  <br>
<br>
I also believe that a vote on something we universally agree on is rather pointless.<br>
<br>
With that in mind, if there aren't any objections, I would like to employ this plan on Friday.  I will go into more depth about the Recruitment Board (specific wording) and First Come, First Serve tomorrow.<br>
<br>
